{"title_page": "Andal\u2013Sainthia branch line", "text_new": "{{short description|Railway line in India}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2012}}\n{{Infobox rail line\n | box_width   = 28em\n | name        = Andal\u2013Sainthia branch line\n | color       =\n | logo        =\n | logo_width  = 100 px\n | image       = Andal-Sainthia Railway Stations.jpg\n | image_width = 300px\n | caption     = Andal railway station and Sainthia railway station\n | type        = Diesel-electric\n | system      = Broad gauge\n | status      = Operational\n | locale      = [[West Bengal]]\n | start       = [[Andal, Bardhaman|Andal]]\n | end         = [[Sainthia Junction]]\n | stations    = 15\n | routes      =\n | daily_ridership =\n | open        = 1913\n | close       =\n | owner       = [[Indian Railway]]\n | operator    = [[Eastern Railway Zone (India)|Eastern Railway]]\n | character   =\n | depot       =\n | stock       =\n | linelength  = {{convert|73|km|mi|0|abbr=on}}\n | tracklength =\n | tracks      =\n | gauge       = {{track gauge|1676mm}} [[Indian gauge|Broad gauge]]\n | old_gauge   =\n | minradius   =\n | racksystem  =\n | electrification =\n | speed       = up to {{convert|100|km/h|abbr=on}}\n | elevation   =\n | website     =\n | map         = {{Andal\u2013Sainthia branch line|inline=1}}\n | map_state   = collapsed\n}}\nThe '''Andal\u2013Sainthia branch line''' is a railway line connecting [[Andal, Bardhaman|Andal]] on the [[Bardhaman\u2013Asansol section]] of the [[Howrah\u2013Delhi Main Line]] and [[Sainthia Junction]] on the [[Sahibganj Loop]]. This {{convert|73|km}} track is under the jurisdiction of [[Eastern Railway Zone (India)|Eastern Railway]].  This track passes through the north-eastern part of the [[Raniganj Coalfield]] in [[Bardhaman district]] and the western part of [[Birbhum district]] in the [[India]]n [[States and territories of India|state]] of [[West Bengal]].\n\nThis track serves [[Bakreshwar Thermal Power Station]].\n\n==History==\nThe Andal\u2013Sainthia branch line was built in 1913.<ref name=timeline>{{cite web|first=R.P.| last=Saxena|title=Indian Railway History Time line|url=http://irse.bravehost.com/IRHTML.htm|work=Irse.bravehost.com|accessdate= 15 March 2017| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120229092028/http://irse.bravehost.com/IRHTML.htm| archivedate=29 February 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Branch lines==\nThere are two branch lines in this section. The first is the Andal\u2013Barabani\u2013Sitarampur section.<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.er.indianrailways.gov.in/view_section.jsp?lang=0&id=0,6,443,528,537 |title =List of Stations on Asansol Division | publisher= Eastern Railway| accessdate = 2011-11-20 }}</ref> The other is the Bhimgara-Palasthali Branch Line. Service on this line was suspended for safety reasons. The track became unfit because of unauthorized mining under the track.<ref>Time Table, July 2005, Eastern Zone</ref>\n\n==Electrification==\nElectrification of Andal\u2013Pandabeshwar section was completed in 2010\u201311.<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.core.indianrailways.gov.in/view_section.jsp?lang=0&id=0,295,329,549 |title = Electrification work in progress by CORE: Progress during the year 2010\u201311| publisher= Central Organisation for Railway Electrification| accessdate = 2011-11-28 }}</ref> Electrification of the Pandabeshwar-Sainthia section was sanctioned in the rail budget for 2011\u201312, which is expected to be completed till 2013 and completed in 2016.<ref>{{cite web| url = http://pib.nic.in/newsite/erelease.aspx?relid=58164|title =Electrification of new rail sections | publisher= Press information Bureau| accessdate = 2011-11-28 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n{{Railway lines in Eastern India}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Andal - Sainthia branch line}}\n[[Category:5 ft 6 in gauge railways in India]]\n[[Category:Rail transport in West Bengal]]\n[[Category:1913 establishments in India]]\n[[Category:Railway lines opened in 1913]]\n[[Category:Transport in Paschim Bardhaman district]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Railway line in India}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2012}}\n{{Infobox rail line\n | box_width   = 28em\n | name        = Andal\u2013Sainthia branch line\n | color       =\n | logo        =\n | logo_width  = 100 px\n | image       = Andal-Sainthia Railway Stations.jpg\n | image_width = 300px\n | caption     = Andal railway station and Sainthia railway station\n | type        = Diesel-electric\n | system      = Broad gauge\n | status      = Operational\n | locale      = [[West Bengal]]\n | start       = [[Andal, Bardhaman|Andal]]\n | end         = [[Sainthia Junction]]\n | stations    = 15\n | routes      =\n | daily_ridership =\n | open        = 1913\n | close       =\n | owner       = [[Indian Railway]]\n | operator    = [[Eastern Railway Zone (India)|Eastern Railway]]\n | character   =\n | depot       =\n | stock       =\n | linelength  = {{convert|73|km|mi|0|abbr=on}}\n | tracklength =\n | tracks      =\n | gauge       = {{track gauge|1676mm}} [[Indian gauge|Broad gauge]]\n | old_gauge   =\n | minradius   =\n | racksystem  =\n | electrification =\n | speed       = up to {{convert|100|km/h|abbr=on}}\n | elevation   =\n | website     =\n | map         = {{Andal\u2013Sainthia branch line|inline=1}}\n | map_state   = collapsed\n}}\nThe '''Andal\u2013Sainthia branch line''' is a railway line connecting [[Andal, Bardhaman|Andal]] on the [[Bardhaman\u2013Asansol section]] of the [[Howrah\u2013Delhi Main Line]] and [[Sainthia Junction]] on the [[Sahibganj Loop]]. This {{convert|73|km}} track is under the jurisdiction of [[Eastern Railway Zone (India)|Eastern Railway]].  This track passes through the north-eastern part of the [[Raniganj Coalfield]] in [[Bardhaman district]] and the western part of [[Birbhum district]] in the [[India]]n [[States and territories of India|state]] of [[West Bengal]].\n\nThis track serves [[Bakreshwar Thermal Power Station]].\n\n==History==\nThe Andal\u2013Sainthia branch line was built in 1913.<ref name=timeline>{{cite web|first=R.P.| last=Saxena|title=Indian Railway History Time line|url=http://irse.bravehost.com/IRHTML.htm|work=Irse.bravehost.com|accessdate= 15 March 2017| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120229092028/http://irse.bravehost.com/IRHTML.htm| archivedate=29 February 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Branch lines==\nThere are two branch lines in this section. The first is the Andal\u2013Barabani\u2013Sitarampur section.<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.er.indianrailways.gov.in/view_section.jsp?lang=0&id=0,6,443,528,537 |title =List of Stations on Asansol Division | publisher= Eastern Railway| accessdate = 2011-11-20 }}</ref> The other is the Bhimgara-Palasthali Branch Line. Service on this line was suspended for safety reasons. The track became unfit because of unauthorized mining under the track.<ref>Time Table, July 2005, Eastern Zone</ref>\n\n==Electrification==\nElectrification of Andal\u2013Pandabeshwar section was completed in 2010\u201311.<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.core.indianrailways.gov.in/view_section.jsp?lang=0&id=0,295,329,549 |title = Electrification work in progress by CORE: Progress during the year 2010\u201311| publisher= Central Organisation for Railway Electrification| accessdate = 2011-11-28 }}</ref> Electrification of the Pandabeshwar-Sainthia section was sanctioned in the rail budget for 2011\u201312, which is expected to be completed till 2013 and completed in 2016.<ref>{{cite web| url = http://pib.nic.in/newsite/erelease.aspx?relid=58164|title =Electrification of new rail sections | publisher= Press information Bureau| accessdate = 2011-11-28 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n{{Andal\u2013Sainthia branch line|collapse=yes}}\n{{Railway lines in Eastern India}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Andal - Sainthia branch line}}\n[[Category:5 ft 6 in gauge railways in India]]\n[[Category:Rail transport in West Bengal]]\n[[Category:1913 establishments in India]]\n[[Category:Railway lines opened in 1913]]\n[[Category:Transport 